        <num>CCP 3227</num>
        <heading>3227.  Execution of contracts</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3227.  Execution of contracts
If a person dies before performing an executory contract evidenced by writing, the court may authorize the succession representative to perform the contract, after compliance with Article 3229.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
